I was walking home for the bus stop and i saw a mexican standing on the corner looking at me. so instead of turning left (where he was) i went right, not where my house is, and i looked back and he was still watching me, so i turned left to cross the street and go up a hill into the graveyard, then i was going to sneak through the grave yard and get past him to go home. so i looked down the hill, he dosn't know were i am but he is still standing there. So i start to panic a little. so i walk threw a tiny section of the woods to get to the street and as soon as i come out of the woods(which took like 10 minutes because i got stuck severely on thorns) he ran after me so i took off like a bat out of hell. 

That was pretty much my day, see u guys later.

Today was pretty kick-ass. When school was over I did my homework and called my friend Chris. i said...dude lets go bike riding. He said he needed air in his tire , ill go fill it up and be at your house in a little bit. Well i was bored so I went to his house, he was still trying to find his bike pump. I helped him look, about half an hour later we give up...he asks him mom for some money to by a new pump, she gives him 20 bucks and we venture to cvs. On the way there we went to the gas station and filled his tire there(its directly across from cvs). we had 20 bucks and nothing to do with it. So we go to cvs to buy a drink. we end up buying 6 cans of Red Bull, two packs of Extra, and two things of Bubble Tape. We spent $19 on this crap. We went to my old school and sat on the slide on the playground(its my elementry school) and chucked Red Bull and ate all of the gum at one time. We laughed histaricly for a good 14 minutes (almost choking twice myself). It was so awesome.


Well im going to back out, peace.

Dude, I was so pissed about going to this wedding.....the wedding sucked, but my brother was driving home with me and my cousin paul in the car, i have my headphones on and I see Paul open his mouth really wide, I take off my headphones and my brother is on the phone with my mom and he said, " Mom, where going to Sesame Place." I was like Boo-Ya. It was $40 a head but wtf, nobody cared, we were at Sesame Place. A 20 year old a 19 year old and a 14 year old at Sesame Place together. We had so much fun, Paul said " I haven't stopped smiling since we got here." And it really was true. The camera had run out of batteries after like 9 pictures, but it was still cool. I never wanted to leave. Holy Crap....good times, good times.



We have to make money to go again.
